{
  "texts": [
    "Research in SDT suggests that sustained playful learning involves experiencing a sense of autonomy and competence, which are often richly afforded within game environments (Rigby & Ryan, 2011).",
    "Carefully applying these concepts to the challenge posed by LLMs for expertise development may turn the outlined risks into promising learning opportunities.",
    "The idea is the same as the one exemplified by Papert's approach (1980) to utilize computers as educational tools.",
    "Instead of seeing LLMs as possibilities to outsource task accomplishment, they are understood as tools that can be utilized to engage in a meaningful activity.",
    "The interface, which has been the Logo language in Papert's case (1980), now is, for instance, ChatGPT, allowing to provide prompts that steer the underlying LLM in the desired direction."
  ]
}